com.jfoenix.transitions

Class JFXFillTransition

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.animation.Animation
      • javafx.animation.Transition
        • com.jfoenix.transitions.JFXFillTransition

  • public final class JFXFillTransition
extends javafx.animation.Transition
    This Transition creates an animation, that changes the filling of a pane over a duration. This is done by updating the background property of the pane at regular intervals.

    It starts from the fromValue.

    It stops at the toValue value.

    It's similar to JavaFX FillTransition, however it can be applied on Region instead of shape

    Since:
    2016-03-09

      • duration

        public final javafx.beans.property.ObjectProperty<javafx.util.Duration> durationProperty
        The duration of this JFXFillTransition.

        Note: While the unit of duration is a millisecond, the granularity depends on the underlying operating system and will in general be larger. For example animations on desktop systems usually run with a maximum of 60fps which gives a granularity of ~17 ms.

        Setting duration to value lower than Duration.ZERO will result in IllegalArgumentException.

        See Also:
        getDuration(), setDuration(Duration)
